name: app.R
content:
library(shiny)
library(ggplot2)
library(plotly)
library(dplyr)
library(tibble)
library(sf)

# Get geso as geodata, stored in rds file. 
# tblsf_geso <- readRDS("tblsf_geso.rds") |> 
#   mutate(geso_lbl = paste("geso", GeSo, sep = "_")) |> 
#   arrange(GeSo)

tblsf_geso <-
  read.csv2("geso.csv") |>
  as_tibble() |> 
    st_as_sf(coords = c("x", "y")) |> 
    group_by(GeSo, GeSo_Benam) |> 
    summarise(do_union = FALSE, .groups = "drop") |> 
    st_cast("POLYGON") |> 
    mutate(geso_lbl = paste("geso", GeSo, sep = "_")) |> 
    arrange(GeSo)

# Define UI for application
ui <- fluidPage(
  
  # Application title
  titlePanel("Färglägg GeSo utifrån data"),
  
  # Sidebar with constrained textboxes for numeric inputs 
  sidebarLayout(
    sidebarPanel(
      mapply(
        \(x, y) {
          numericInput(
            inputId = x,
            label = y,
            value = NA,
          )
        },
        tblsf_geso$geso_lbl,
        tblsf_geso$GeSo_Benam,
        SIMPLIFY = FALSE
      ),
    ),
    
    # Show a map
    mainPanel(
      plotlyOutput("plot_geso_val")
    )
  )
)


server <- function(input, output) {
  
  tbl_out <- reactive({
    tblsf_geso |> 
      mutate(geso_value = case_when(
        GeSo == 1  ~ input$geso_1,
        GeSo == 2  ~ input$geso_2,
        GeSo == 3  ~ input$geso_3,
        GeSo == 4  ~ input$geso_4,
        GeSo == 5  ~ input$geso_5,
        GeSo == 6  ~ input$geso_6,
        GeSo == 7  ~ input$geso_7,
        GeSo == 8  ~ input$geso_8,
        GeSo == 9  ~ input$geso_9,
        GeSo == 10 ~ input$geso_10,
        GeSo == 11 ~ input$geso_11,
        GeSo == 12 ~ input$geso_12,
        GeSo == 13 ~ input$geso_13,
        GeSo == 14 ~ input$geso_14,
        .default = NA_real_
      ))
  })
  
  
  output$plot_geso_val <- renderPlotly({
    tbl_temp <- tbl_out()
    
    if (all(is.na(tbl_temp$geso_value))) {
      plot_ly(tbl_out()) |> 
        add_sf(
          type = "scatter", 
          stroke = I("black"), 
          span = I(1), 
          alpha = 1,
          split = ~GeSo_Benam,
          color = I("white")
        ) |> 
        layout(showlegend = FALSE)
    } else {
    plot_ly(tbl_out()) |> 
      add_sf(
        type = "scatter", 
        stroke = I("black"), 
        span = I(1), 
        alpha = 1,
        split = ~GeSo_Benam,
        color = ~geso_value,
        colors = "Reds"
      ) |> 
        layout(showlegend = FALSE)
    }
  })
  
  # output$plot_geso_val <- renderPlotly({
  # ggplotly(
  #   ggplot(tbl_out(), aes(fill = geso_value)) +
  #     geom_sf() +
  #     theme_void() +
  #     scale_fill_continuous(na.value="white")
  # )
  # })
  
  # output$plot_geso_val <- plotly::renderPlotly({
  #   plotly::ggplotly(ggplot(tbl_out(), aes(x = 1, y=geso_value)) + 
  #                      geom_point())
  # })
}


shinyApp(ui, server)
